properties.name: Skydive Alabama

properties.name: Skydive The South

properties.description: Open weekends and most holidays. Conveniently located off I-85 at historic Moton Airfield. Only minutes from Auburn and Montgomery area.

properties.name: Alaska Skydive Center

Cessna 206 drop zone.

properties.name: Phoenix Area Skydiving

properties.name: Red Rock Skydiving, LLC

From either city, take exit 287 and follow 260 west to Cottonwood. Take 89A south to Mingus Ave. and turn left. The DZ is the second airport entrance on the left. Indoor packing area.

properties.name: Skydive Arizona
properties.description: Largest fleet of skydiving aircraft: 4 Super Twin Otters, 5 Super Skyvans, Pilatus Porter, DC-3, Hot Air Balloons & 14 foot SkyVenture Wind Tunnel. World champion coaches and organizers. Pool, restaurant/bar, team rooms, bunkhouse, motel, rigging loft, gear store and indoor packing. 50 miles south of Phoenix off I-10.

properties.name: Skydive Phoenix
properties.description: Skydive Phoenix is located just 20 miles south of downtown Phoenix. Open 7 days a week year round. We pride ourselves in making your experience safe, fun, and memorable. We welcome all levels of jumpers, from first-timers to the experienced. We offer multiple disciplines of instruction, specializing in tandem student training.

properties.name: Skydive Skyranch
properties.description: Open Fridays and weekends featuring a carpeted packing area, pea gravel pit and 280 HP Cessna 182's. Twin Beech also available.

properties.name: Bay Area Skydiving
properties.description: At Bay Area Skydiving, we offer a fun and friendly, family-based DZ for all to enjoy. We are centrally located to the Bay Area, San Francisco, and the Central Valley. We vary in skydives from RW, freeflying, skysurfing and whatever else we can come up with. All are welcome! Open Wednesday through Sunday year round.

properties.name: Madera Parachute Center
properties.description: Open Saturday and Sunday. Huge on-airport landing area and grass or hangar packing areas. 10,500-ft. altitude with great view of Sierra Nevadas and San Joaquin Valley. Friendly, unpretentious, family atmosphere. Activities for non-jumpers close by (golf, theater and shopping). All skill levels welcome.

properties.name: NorCal Skydiving
properties.description: Located in California Wine Country at Cloverdale Airport. Views of the Alexander Valley, Pacific Ocean and Mount Shasta from 13000 feet. See www.norcalskydiving.com for reservations and directions.

properties.name: Pacific Coast Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week year-round. We are mostly a tandem drop zone. We have RVT video technology and scenic flights over the ocean before every jump. Located just 20 minutes from downtown San Diego.

properties.name: Santa Cruz Skydiving / Skydive Surf City, Inc
properties.description: Open six days a week, year round (closed Wednesdays). We are predominately a Tandem operation. Just off highway 1, 15 minutes south of Santa Cruz, exit: Freedom Airport Blvd.

properties.name: SkyDance SkyDiving
properties.description: Quality skydiving in Northern California. Home of the 30,000 ft. skydives and host to the Olympic Skydiving Team. Complete facilities and Pro Shop (Action Air Parachutes). Freeflying and formation coaching available. Open daily. Close to San Francisco, Napa Valley, Lake Tahoe and Sacramento.

properties.name: Skydive California
properties.description: Open five days a week, all year round. Located on our own private airstrip that is only one hour east of the San Francisco Bay Area. Air-conditioned packing area. Excellent coaching staff!

properties.name: Skydive Coastal California
properties.description: Tandem Skydiving only 40 minutes from Los Angeles. Beautiful Ocean views on a scenic flight to altitude and during 120 mph freefall. From Los Angeles take the 101 north to Camarillo exit 55 for Las Posas Road and turn left. Go 1 mile to Pleasent Valley Road and turn right. Go 1/2 mile to Airport Way and turn right. Go 1/4 mile to Durley Ave and turn left. Park at the Way Point Cafe on the right. We are in the camarillo Aircraft Service building to the left of the Cafe.

properties.name: Skydive Elsinore
properties.description: Open year round! One hour from San Diego and Los Angeles. Nestled in the scenic recreational valley of Lake Elsinore, CA. Beautiful lake and ocean views nestled in the surrounding San Bernadino and Ortega Mountains. FS, FF and WS organizing and coaching available. Covered packing and creeping areas. Known as one of the worlds friendliest drop-zone. Please feel free to contact us so that we can assist you in planning your stay.

properties.name: Skydive Hollister
properties.description: Phones on 7 days a week from 10am-4pm. We jump Friday through Monday from sunrise to sunset. Just 45 miles south of San Jose. Take the 101 south and merge on to hwy 25. We run a PAC 750 and rent gear from 150 sq ft to 265 sq ft.

properties.name: Skydive Monterey Bay
properties.description: Open seven days, year round. King Air 90 series jumps to 15k & 18k. Ocean view. From San Francisco, take 101-south to hwy 156 W to Monterey Peninsula, then hwy 1 south to Reservation Rd exit, then left at Imjin Rd into Marina Municipal Airport, left on Neeson Rd. Coaching available.

properties.name: Skydive Perris
properties.description: Club Med of Skydiving! Wind tunnel on-site. Open 365 days a year. Free load organizing for all disciplines on weekends. Facilities include: fully equipped house, bar, and video rooms. Indoor Skydiving Simulator, Square One with full rigging services on DZ. 1.5 hour drive to LAX airport; beaches, mountains, amusement parks and Hollywood. A true family vacation combination!

properties.name: Skydive Sacramento
properties.description: Open Wednesday through Sunday. Take Freeway 80 to 65 North. Exit right onto Nelson. Turn left onto Nicolas Rd, then right onto Airport Rd.

properties.name: Skydive San Diego
properties.description: Come out and jump two twin otters over beautiful sunny San Diego. Views of the mountains, ocean and Mexico on every jump. Gear sales, food and coaching available.

properties.name: Skydive San Joaquin Valley
properties.description: Skydive San Joaquin Valley is located at DB Cooper Field about 75 miles north of Los Angeles. Check out our website for more details!

properties.name: Skydive Santa Barbara, LLC
properties.description: Open seven days a week. Check the website for directions. www.skydivesantabarbara.com Just 15 minutes from the ocean. 18,000 ft jumps available! Jumpers with less than 1000 jumps are required to use an AAD.

properties.name: Skydive Taft
properties.description: Open Friday, Saturday and Sunday only. One hour and 45 minutes north of L.A. RV parking available. Freefly and RW coaching available!

properties.name: Tsunami Skydivers

properties.name: Mile-Hi Skydiving Center, Inc.
properties.description: Nestled against the Rocky Mountains and less than 25 miles from the Denver metro area. Three new hangars complete with all modern facilities and indoor packing. All disciplines welcome. Boulder, a mecca for outdoor sports, is just a 15 minute drive. Open year-round on weekends and seven days a week spring through fall.

properties.name: Out Of The Blue Skydiving
properties.description: Located at the Fremont County Airport. We are less than an hour from both Colorado Springs and Pueblo. Our student services include tandem and AFF. Experienced jumpers also welcome. Full-time rigging loft.

properties.name: Skydive Colorado
properties.description: Open 5-7 days a week. Six miles from Canon City on Hwy 50. Come see the Royal Gorge and float the Arkansas River after your jump!

properties.name: Connecticut Parachutists, Inc.
properties.description: One of New England's premier skydiving centers. Open Thursday-Sunday April through October. Weekends only December through November. Freeflying, RW, CRW, Wingsuiting and accuracy. Covered packing areas, bonfire pit and great skydiving! Check out our website for featured events. Come learn, fun jump or take a tandem at CPI. Home of Champions.

properties.name: Skydive Danielson
location: 28 miles W of Providence, RI; 48 miles E of Hartford, CT
properties.description: Open 7 days a week, April-November. Tri-State border MA/CT/RI. I-395 exit 93. West on CT 101/Hartford Pike. Left on Upper Maple St. Right on Airport Rd.

properties.name: Skydive Delmarva, Inc.
properties.description: Open six days a week (Wednesday-Monday). Covered packing with TVs and DVD players, and covered creeping. Wide-open landing area. 30 minutes from Delaware and Maryland beaches. Easy access from Washington DC, Baltimore, Annapolis, Wilmington and Philadelphia.

properties.name: Florida Skydiving Center/Skydive Lake Wales
location: 50 miles SW of Orlando/ 50 miles SE of Tampa
properties.description: We have 250 acres of wide-open landing area. Instruction is available to all levels of skydivers. Friendly staff. Please call for hours of operation. For summer hours please call first.

properties.name: Jump Florida Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. We have fun and friendly staff!

We specialize in student training. Scenic flights over the ocean are included with most jumps. Enjoy views of the Miami skyline, Biscayne Bay, the Florida Keys and much more. Jumps are only a few miles from the ocean.

properties.name: North Florida Skydiving
properties.description: Mostly a weekend drop zone. 10 miles off of I-75; 40 min from Valdosta, GA. Tandem, AFF and Coach instruction available. Packing area in hangar. Lunch available on-site.

properties.name: School of Human Flight
properties.description: We serve Tallahassee, Panama City, Destin, Ft Walton, Dothan & Valdosta. Friendly family atmosphere. All disciplines are welcome. Beautiful sunsets. Memorable parties. Rigging services available on a drop off basis. Call ahead for scheduling.

properties.name: Skydive Amelia Island
properties.description: Open year round. Located 34 miles north of Jacksonville. Cessna tandem operation with great views!!

properties.name: Skydive City Zephyrhills
properties.description: Florida's Skydiving Resort. We have full amenities for your vacation and training. Food, laundry, camping, trailers for rent, rigging, gear sales, rating school, bar, internet access and much more. We also have RVs available for rent!

properties.name: Skydive DeLand Inc

Open full time 365 days per year.

properties.name: Skydive Jacksonville
properties.description: Open 7 days a week. Located 11 miles west of Jacksonville at Herlong Airport off of Normandy Blvd.

properties.name: Skydive Key West

properties.name: Skydive Miami

We offer great rates, so come jump with us out of our 15-place Turbine Caravan and enjoy our modern indoor air-conditioned facilities for a fantastic holiday. We look forward to seeing you at Skydive Miami.

properties.name: Skydive North Florida
properties.description: Open Saturday, Sunday and military/holiday 4-day weekends. 60 miles northeast of Panama City, FL. Spend the weekend! 5000sqf indoor packing/sleeping area, RV hookups, 20 acre landing area with 100's of acres of "outs". Cessna 182 and PAC750 in the winter. All disciplines with coaching, inexpensive military transitions. VERY family friendly!

properties.name: Skydive Palatka
properties.description: Skydive Palatka is near the St. Johns River. We have new facilities, including a training room and a large covered packing area. November activities include the annual Hog Flop Boogie.

properties.name: Skydive Palm Beach
properties.description: Located at Palm Beach County Glades Airport--just 25 miles west of West Palm Beach. 561-JumpNow or skydivepalmbeach.com

properties.name: Skydive Sebastian
properties.description: Skydiving over the Florida Coastline! Tandem Skydives, (AFF) Accelerated Freefall Student Courses, and "destination" or a "home" drop zone for Experienced Skydivers. RW, Freefly, CReW, and Canopy coaching available. Load organizing, Beach Jumps, Zoo Bar & Cafe. Located on the Florida Coastline allowing visiting skydivers to enjoy an amazing view of the Sebastian Inlet and the Atlantic Ocean while in freefall and under canopy as well as a coastal environment after skydiving.

properties.name: Skydive Space Center
properties.description: 30 minutes from Orlando. Take 528 E to 95 N to Exit 220. East on Garden St. 1.3 miles, turn left onto Williams Ave. Open seven days a week.

properties.name: Skydive Spaceland-Clewiston

properties.name: SW Florida Skydive Club

properties.name: World Skydiving Center Florida

properties.name: Skydive Atlanta
properties.description: Open Friday, Saturday and Sunday year-round. Full-service DZ. Located just off I-75, one hour from Atlanta, Macon, and Columbus. Large, open landing areas. properties.name: Skydive Georgia
properties.description: Open seven days a week. One hour northwest of Atlanta. Our facilities offer free bunk room, wireless internet and of course air conditioned and carpeted packing area.

properties.name: Skydive Spaceland-Atlanta
properties.description: Freefall over the scenic hills of Georgia just 45 miles northwest of downtown Atlanta! Our completely remodeled facility is open everyday- except Christmas-on our own private airfield. We have state-of-the-art gear and offer training to become a skydiver in as little as a week! We fly a Super Otter, Super Caravan and/or a Super SkyVan daily. Also, convenient to Birmingham, AL and Chattanooga, TN.

properties.name: The Jumping Place

Call 912-322-7282 for the gate access code.

properties.name: Pacific Skydiving Center

Safety is our number one priority. Our beautiful drop zone is open 364 days a year. Closed only on Christmas day. We have an international staff, coaching, great jump planes, A/C in all rooms, top of the line equipment, services and value. Jump in paradise! Check out our website: www.pacificskydivinghawaii.com

properties.name: Sky Down Skydiving
properties.description: Open 365 days a year. A friendly, yet professional environment where safety always comes first. Huge facility with easy I-84 access. 2500 foot indoor climate controlled packing room. Large grass landing area for experienced jumpers. Multiple landing areas to accommodate all skill levels. Breathtaking view of Lake Lowell, Boise valley, the Snake River and Owyhee Mountains. Come jump with us for one of the most scenic views in Idaho!

properties.name: Skydive Idaho
properties.description: Owned and operated by world record holders and USPA Nationals medalist. Skydive Idaho operates on a private runway covering 150 acres of scenic landscape and grass parachute landing area. We also have two covered picnic areas for your parties and/or events. Visit the dropzone where our fun, safe, and professional staff won't treat you like a number. All skill levels welcome. Wingsuit School and Freefly Instruction also available. Jump with the best!

properties.name: Chicagoland Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open seven days a week. Home of the "Sweet Fleet". Some of the nicest super otter and PAC 750XLs in skydiving.

properties.name: Illinois Skydiving Center
properties.description: Weekdays by appointment. 8:00am - Sunset during weekends. Located 4 miles southeast of Rantoul on a private airstrip. No airport hassles. Larger aircraft for special events.

properties.name: Illinois Valley Parachute Club

properties.name: SEMO Skydiving
properties.description: Small friendly DZ, open weekends year round. Indoor packing and spacious landing area. Located 30 miles southeast of Cape Girardeau, MO just off I-57.

properties.name: Skydive Chicago Inc
properties.description: The midwest's largest skydiving resort. From the Chicago area, I-55 south to I-80W, Exit 93, 71 north to Dayton Road and turn right. Host of the 2016 World Championships. properties.description: Open weekends only. 30 miles south of Chicago. Exit 308 on I57 to 60 south then 1.5 miles to Airport Road West. Personalized tandem instruction, relaxed atmosphere, restricted access, excellent hangar and facilities. Weekdays by appointment only.

properties.name: Jerry's Skydiving Circus
properties.description: Open Easter-Thanksgiving; Thursday and Friday afternoons, and Saturday and Sunday from 10am to dark. Tandems by appointment. Inside carpeted packing area.

properties.name: Plymouth Sky Sports

properties.name: Skydive Greater Michigan City
properties.description: Tandem Skydiving! Open 7 days a week, April-November. 62 driving and 40 nautical miles from downtown Chicago. Great views of the Chicago skyline and minutes from Michigan City beaches and outlet malls. Skydive Greater Michigan City and Kankakee, Il locations focus on Tandem Skydiving and Training, to ensure customer satisfaction.

properties.description: Open seven days a week, March 1-November 15. From Indianapolis go I-65 north (25 min) to exit 158. Go east two miles to Frankfort Airport. Coaching available.

properties.name: Des Moines Skydivers, LLC
properties.description: Only 15 minutes from I-35 and I-80. Open weekends and some weekdays--call the dropzone for jumping information. Turbine aircraft available June-September. Home of the Couch Freaks.

properties.name: Air Capital Drop Zone

properties.name: Kansas State University Parachute Club
properties.description: Located near the great college town of Manhattan, KSUPC is one of the oldest collegiate parachute clubs in existence. Open weekends and some weekdays all year long. First-jump courses are scheduled regularly, and visitors are welcome. Carpeted packing.

properties.name: Skydive Gypsy Moths
properties.description: (1K1) Stearman Field in Benton, Kansas--just 10 miles NE of Wichita. The movie, The Gypsy Moths, was filed right here at our airport in 1969! Amenities include 2 clean Cessna 182s, carpeted, heated and fan-cooled hangar with restroom and shower, overnight rooms are available on the airport. A restaurant and bar are at Stearman Field Bar & Grill.

properties.name: Skydive Kansas
location: 30 miles S of Topeka; 30 miles W of Ottawa; 35 miles NE of Emporia
properties.description: From Topeka, take 75 S to 31 W. Open weekends year-round and some weekdays during the summer. (Call first during winter months) Large carpeted indoor packing area. properties.name: Skydive Kentucky

properties.name: Skydive Nawlins.com

properties.name: Skydive New England

The only swoop pond in New England!

properties.name: Vacationland Skydiving

properties.name: Skydive Harbor Springs

properties.name: Skydive Snohomish, Inc.
properties.description: A welcoming atmosphere, convenient location, excellent equipment, and breathtaking scenery are what make Snohomish, an exceptional skydive training and recreation center. Visit our website and see for yourself the 360-degree scenic landscape, aircraft, first-class facilities, hours of operation and detailed driving directions.

properties.name: Skydive Toledo
properties.description: Friendly drop zone located between Portland, Oregon and Olympia, Wash. View of Mt. St. Helens and Cascade mountain range. Open year-round. AFF and Coach Examiner on site. All jumpers welcome!

properties.name: West Plains Skydiving -The Ritz-
properties.description: Open Saturday and Sunday April-November, occasionally weeknights. From Spokane, travel west on I-90 to exit #226 and drive 1/4 mile on Schoessler Rd. Indoor packing.

properties.name: Great Lakes Skydiving
properties.description: Open seven days a week March-November. Indoor packing. Tandem and Coach Examiners and rigger on staff. 2 miles from Exit 1 off I-39-I90.

properties.name: Seven Hills Skydivers of Madison, WI
properties.description: Located approximately 15 minutes north of Madison on a rural, picturesque airport. Friendly, non-profit club owned and operated. Established in 1962. Large, comfortable clubhouse with indoor heated and air-conditioned packing area. Great camping and picnic areas on the DZ. Open Wednesday afternoons in summer (4-sunset) and weekends (9-sunset) year round (weather providing).

properties.name: Skydive Midwest
location: 50 miles N of Chicago, 30 miles S of Milwaukee
properties.description: Open seven days a week. April-November. We offer tandem, AFF and welcome experienced skydiver. From Chicago take I-94 north to Exit 335, turn left. When you reach South Sylvania Ave. turn right. From Milwaukee take I-94 south to Exit 333 turn right on Hwy 20 then left on S Sylvania.

properties.name: Skydive Milwaukee/Sky Knights Sport Parachute Club
properties.description: Open seven days a week April-October and weekends in the winter. Closed-in packing area. Heated and air-conditioned office, classrooms and video area. Two-story lounge and theater with observation deck. Large grill available for cookouts. Lots of grass and landing area with swoop course for all skydiving needs.

properties.name: Skydive Superior
properties.description: Located at the top of Wisconsin on the very tip of the largest fresh water lake (Superior) in the world! Family owned and operated, Skydive Superior offers breathtaking views and friendly people. Brand new state-of-the-art hangar with new training, packing and lounge areas. Camping available. Open year round and New Years Eve jumps available. R-44 Helicopter and Turbine Aircraft also available. Celebrating our 55th year. We are one of America's oldest drop zones!

properties.name: Skydive Twin Cities
properties.description: Weekdays 10:00am until sunset. Weekends 8:00am until sunset. From Twin Cities take I-94 E. into Wisconsin to Exit 16 or the Hammond Exit. Go north 1.5 miles to County Rd. J. Go east two miles, the airport is on the north side of County Rd. J. Indoor packing available. Super Grand Caravan available during summer season.

properties.name: Skydive Wissota/Indianhead SPC
properties.description: Open weekends year-round and Wednesday evenings during Daylight Savings Time. Located near Lake Wissota and State Park. Air-conditioned and heated club house.

properties.name: Wisconsin Skydiving Center
properties.description: Located at Fort Atkinson Municipal Airport along the scenic Rock River. Beautiful new facilities. Indoor packing. Fast-climbing 182s (12,500 ft. in twenty minutes). AFF examiner, tandem examiner, and master rigger on staff. Thirty-five years of experience. Safe, fun skydiving. Enjoy no politics! Relaxed AtmospAIR!

properties.name: World Skydiving Center
properties.description: Open seven days a week from April 15th to October 15th. From Chicago, take 94 North the Exit 342. Turn East of Rt 158(52nd St) for one mile to Kenosha Regional Airport.

properties.name: Paracenter
properties.description: Open 365 days a year. Carpeted indoor packing area, snack bar and bunkhouse available. Rigging services and FF coaching offered.

properties.name: Skydive Rosario
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. 15 minutes from Rosario City (Santa Fe). Coaching available for Free Fly, Angle Fly, RW, Wingsuite, and Canopy Piloting.

properties.name: Skydive Spa
properties.description: Open full-time between April and October; otherwise just weekends. Only full-time professional DZ in Belgium. Situated in the Belgium Ardennes nest to the FI race track-Spa Francorchamps, 1.5 hrs from Brussels, close to the Dutch and Belgium border.

properties.name: Sky Company Clube e Escola de Paraquedismo
properties.description: Sky Company-Brazil-Boituva-SP. National Center Skydiving. Coaching, Tandem jumps and AFF instruction offered.

properties.name: SkyRadical Boituva
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. One hour from Sao Paulo (Capital). Rooms available for teams. Coaching available.

properties.name: Skydive Sofia
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. From capital Sofia, take E-80 to exit 01 Ihtiman, 40 km from Sofia Airport. Heated hanger. Restaurant, swimming pool, volleyball, football, golf club, horse riding, quad and motorcycle bike rental, basketball and soccer fields located at the hotel just 3 km from the DZ! Coaching available in RW, Freefly, Style and Accuracy.

properties.name: Eden North Parachute Schools
properties.description: Eden North is a full service parachute center operating Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday and all holidays from May 1-October 31. We are located 25 miles west of Edmonton on highway 16, north 4 miles on Range Road #20 and west one mile on Township Road 540.

properties.name: Niagara Skydive Centre, Inc
properties.description: Niagara Skydive Centre is a full-time skydive facility from May to October. First class facilities and training, located a short distance from the Greater Toronto area. Friendly atmosphere with free camping and shower facilities. We operate a Navajo (10 passenger) and Cessna for your skydiving needs. Very scenic view!

properties.name: Parachutisme Adrenaline St-Jerome
properties.description: Open seven days a week, all summer from May to October. From Montreal City, take I-15 north to exit 43 west. Rigging loft on site, camping available.

properties.name: Skydive Burnaby
properties.description: Open seven days a week, seasonally. Directions can be found on our website. Airlift Caravan. Planned events scheduled every weekend. Load organizing and coaching available. Breathtaking views with every jump. Located between Lake Erie and Lake Ontario. Come visit us today!

properties.name: Skydive Gananoque
properties.description: Located in the scenic Thousand Islands area of Eastern Ontario. Skydive Gananoque (pronounced GAN-AN-OCK-WAY) is midway between Montreal and Toronto and a 20 minute drive from the Canada/US border of upstate New York. Open seven days a week April-October. Coaching available on weekends (freestyle, style & accuracy and RW).

properties.name: Skydive the City
properties.description: Vancouver's closest skydive center! We are a small twin Cessna operation, right beside the beautiful coastal mountains. Great facilities, but no camping available. Call before you arrive.

properties.name: Skydive Vancouver
properties.description: 2 turbine full-service DZ. Open 7 days a week. 1 hour from Vancouver and 2 hours from Seattle. Home of the first USA-Canada Nationals!

properties.name: Tuofeng Skydiving Puer
properties.description: Open all year round. Close to the spring city, Kunming. Located inside of Puer airport. Regular flights from Kunming International Airport to Puer. Nice staff members and friendly instructors. Good hotels and quality restaurants nearby.

properties.name: Tuofeng Skydiving Shijiazhuang
properties.description: Open all year round. Close to the capital, Beijing. Takes a short trip from Beijing by train or you can land in Schijiazhuang Airport and drive one hour to the DZ. Nice staff and friendly instructors. Good hotels and quality restaurants nearby.

properties.name: Desafio Vertical
properties.description: This is a small operation dedicated to building up the skydiver base in Costa Rica. Active 2 weekends a month with S/L students and a few up-jumpers. No amenities, but super friendly staff to compensate!

properties.name: Skydive Costa Rica
properties.description: Enjoy one of the best views in the world! Jump into the tropics!

properties.name: Padobranski Sportski Klub Slobodan Pad
properties.description: Our drop zone is located 25 km east of Zagreb City, beside the town of Vrbovec. We are closed from November 1-April 1. Most jump activities are during weekends, but we can organize activities during the week as well. There are bathrooms, a small bar and a packing area available. Please call before arriving call 091-4290-926 to check for activity on the drop zone.

properties.name: Dropzone Prostejov
properties.description: Organizer of the World Championships 2014, European Championships 2005,2009,2012, World Cup 2009,2012, and the Vector Festival 2011,2012. Free DZ transportation from Brno Intl. Airport. Open on weekends; 7 days a week during the summer. 4000m (13130ft) from 19,90â‚¬. Coaching available in FF, FS, and SU. Please check our website for more information

properties.name: DZ Pribram
properties.description: DZ open Friday-Sunday; 7 days a week during the summer. From capital city of Prague, take R4 Highway in the direction of Strakonice, Exit 41-follow the white signs "Letiste/Airport" (30 mins drive time). Coaching in formation skydiving and freefly available. Air conditioned hotel with restaurant located at the DZ. L-410 Turbolet & AN-2.

properties.name: International Pink Parachute Club
properties.description: Open May and August. Also available on site: Child Day Care & Team Rooms. See website for dates and additional boogies of the Pink Skyvan in Europe. From Prague International Airport, follow signs to Plzen. In Plzen, follow signs to Klatovy. The drop zone is approximately one km. north of Klatovy on the street to Nepomuk. Follow signs to "Letiste".

properties.name: Dropzone Denmark
properties.description: Open 7 days a week from April to October. Only full-time drop zone in Denmark. 3 miles from Herning. Billund Int'l airport is 40 miles away. Large hangar, full-service cafe/bar, full packing area and Europe's larges swoop pond! FS/Freefly coaching available everyday. We will accommodate your every need.

properties.name: Skydive Finland
properties.description: We are open mainly during the summer months from April to September at DZ Utti, which is located 150 km from the capital.

properties.name: Skydive Karjala
properties.description: Take highway 6 northeast from Imatra, to exit B right after a large paper mill on the left. Take the exit and turn right to the airfield. Bunkhouse, teamrooms, covered and indoor packing areas. Sauna and swimming at nearby lake.

properties.name: Air 65
properties.description: Open from March to November. Next to the Pyrenees Mountains. AFF, tandem, relative work, freefly and canopy piloting formation training available. Pilatus Porter, clubhouse, hangar and student rigs available. Offering camping, hotel and bed & breakfast accommoodations all within one mile of the drop zone. One hour driving distance from Toulouse Airport and one hour from Pau Airport.

properties.name: ParisJump
properties.description: ParisJump is one of the nearest DZ's to Paris (170 km). AFF facilities are available on weekends and one week a month. We are located in the Bourgogne region with is famous for it's bourguignon beef and wine (Charlis is approx. 15 min away). Load organizers are available. See you soon!

properties.name: Peronne
properties.description: 1 hour from Paris, 45 min from Charles de Gauble Airport, the nearest DZ to Paris. Open Friday to Monday inclusive every weekend and one week per month. Please contact us for more information.

properties.name: AIRCREW & Airfox Skydiving Academy
location: 50 km S of Munich and 4 km E of Bad Toelz
properties.description: Professional full-time skydiving school and rating academy. By appointment only, please.

properties.name: FSC Suedpfalz E.V.
properties.description: Lovely dropzone in the southwest of Germany near the French border and the "Deutsche Weintor". Perfect for teams or solo jumpers. RW and freefly coaching available at a low price. Wingsuit rental and coaching available. Inside packing area, Packer, gear rental, restaurant, videographers, team room and load organizing. Open from March to November, Friday - Sunday and in the week on inquiry. Camping and hotels just 5 km. away. Sleep possible in bunkhouse, please bring your airbed.

properties.name: Skydive Exit
properties.description: 100 km east of Munich. Very comfortable lounges. Indoor packing. Skydive operation from March to September every day except Mondays; weekends all year round upon request. AFF instruction and Tandems. RW, Freefly and Wingsuit coaching available.

properties.name: Skydive Nuggets
properties.description: Open seven days a week April-October. One hour drive from Munich, 1.5 hour drive from Stuttgart. AFF instruction, tandem, 4-way to 8-way coaching, freefly coaching. One of the biggest drop zones in South Germany.

properties.name: Skydive Saulgau
properties.description: Open Friday through Sunday year-round. Open almost everyday in the summer. From Ulm, take B30 direction to Friedrichshafen. Indoor packing. Jaccuzzi and terrace. Very friendly staff. Coaching available for RW and FF.

properties.name: Southsidebase
location: 50 km SE of Frankfurt and Stuttgart
properties.description: Open from March to October. Between Frankfurt and Stuttgart, full service, Seven days a week July, August and September. Coaching in freefly, RW and wingsuit.

properties.name: Hellenic Skydivers
properties.description: DZ's atmosphere is friendly. The view over the airport is stunning.You can see the historic cities of Athens, Piraeus and the ancient battle places of Marathon and Salamis. There are several motels and restaurants at very reasonable prices.

properties.name: Skydive Balaton
location: 5 km S of Siofok, 100 km SW of Budapest
properties.description: DZ is near Siofok town at Lake Balaton; 1 hour from Budapest, shuttle available. Season is from April 1 till November 1. DZ open on weekends and also weekdays during organized events. Each Mi-8 helicopter can accommodate up to 29 jumpers/load. There are restaurants, air-conditioned accommodations up to 80 people and 9 hangars for packing. Please contact in advance before arriving. For more details check www.skydivebalaton.com

properties.name: Skyriders
properties.description: Open seven days a week. Mysore DZ is 146 km from the capital city, Bangolore. Connected by rail, air and road, the airport has all major facilities; air traffic control, meteorological department, and modern first aid and ambulance services. The scenic beauty is a feast for the eyes while skydiving!

properties.name: Irish Parachute Club, Ltd.
properties.description: The Irish Parachute Club is over 50 years of operation. We do approximately 10,000 jumps annually. We run static line, tandem and AFF courses every weekend. There are about 160 regular members. Located 64 km from our capital city, Dublin, which is an hour drive from the DZ. Our club is open every weekend all year round.

properties.name: Sky Kef
properties.description: Open every weekend year-round. One hour drive from major cities. Sunshine and warm temperatures 360 days a year.

properties.name: A.S. Alimarche
properties.description: Open weekends year-round and every day from June 1st to August 31st. On the Adriatic Sea. The home of Sinapsi 4 way team. Coaching, load organizing and beach jumps every sunset during the summer time.

properties.name: Area Delta 47
properties.description: Open Friday, Saturday and Sunday. Close to Casale Monferrato Sud highway exit. Coaching available in formation skydiving and freeflying.

properties.name: Scuola Paracadutismo Lucca
properties.description: Open only during weekends and National holidays. Highway exit "Capannori"

properties.name: Skydive FlyGang--Moli DZone
properties.description: We are the biggest DZ in Italy open weekdays in summer. Open 7-7 from May to October. Located just 15 miles from Bologna International Airport (BLQ). Professional, and friendly staff--all are USPA and Skydive University rated. Load organizers and coaching for all disciplines. We also offer drop zone van and bike rentals. English, French and Spanish spoken. We have very special rates...just ask!

properties.name: Skydive Pull Out
properties.description: Open every Saturday & Sunday from 8:00 am to sunset and everyday during the summertime! DZ organizes events, boogies, beach jumps, Wingsuit Internatinal Competitions, and Canopy Piloting Championships. NEW--Swoop training, RW, Freefly, Wingsuit, and Canopy coaching! Load organizing and rigging service. Great panoramic view over the Adriatic Sea and vast landing area. Skydiving shop, restaurant, and swimming pool for relaxing!

properties.name: Skydive Sardegna
properties.description: Open all weekends, organizing coach/instructor courses and Boogies over Christmas (everyday activity for a whole month in December/January) and Summer (30 days activity in August with landings on the beach). The mild climate 365 days a year, the incredible landscape and the delicious Sardinian food are guarantees for great fun.

properties.name: The Zoo Skydiving
properties.description: Open weekends year round and weekdays for groups of at least 12 jumpers. Cessna Short Caravan. Coaching available in Formation skydiving, Freeflying, Wingsuit, and Canopy Piloting. AFF and Tandem instruction offered. Bunkhouse, hot shower, summer pool available. Tourism sites are just a short distance away! We have a second website available---> www.skydivethezoo.weebly.com

properties.name: Skydive Fujioka
properties.description: Open every weekend and some weekdays. Closest drop zone to Tokyo--only one hour travel time! 10 minutes to 12,500 ft!

properties.name: Skydiving Kansai
properties.description: Open seven days a week year round. Located at Tajima Airport. About 15 minutes by car to DZ from Toyooka City.

properties.name: Tokyo Skydiving Club
properties.description: National 4-way and 8-way teams' home drop zone. The DZ is located in Saitama prefecture about 40km from Tokyo. Open 5-6 days a week. Contact DZ office before visiting. Bunkhouse with bath available within 500m of DZ.

properties.name: Skydive Diani
properties.description: Open 7 days a week all year round. Voted by Yahoo as "One of the most scenic places to skydive in the world"! The drop zone is located right next to the Indian Ocean. We offer a restaurant, bar, packing area, dirt diving area with creepers, pool, and sunset BBQ's.

properties.name: Skydive Latvia
properties.description: DZ is open weekends during the summer.

properties.name: Skydive Cuautla
properties.description: With an atmosphere of an outdoor vacation getaway, Mexico's only turbine DZ offers a skydiving experience centered around customer service. Load organizing and coaching available in RW and Freefly. Excellent AFF and Tandem programs. The year round beautiful weather makes us a popular destination. Visit www.skydivecuautla.com for more information and directions.

properties.name: Skydive Taroudant
properties.description: Open 7 days a week from December 15 to March 31. Over 300 days of sun and a family atmosphere! 70 km from the International Airport of Ayadir. 4 km east of the historical ancient capital of Morocco, Gate of the Desert and is beside the Atlas Mountains.

properties.name: Swakopmund Skydiving Club
properties.description: We operate 7 days a week from 9am to 30 minutes before sunset. We are situated at the Swakopmund Airport; approximately 3 km from Swakopmund on the B2 toward Windhoek. Our closest international airports are Windhoek and Walvis Bay. Shuttle services are available. We have a restaurant, bar, pool and BBQ area available. We also offer WIFI, indoor air conditioned packing area, debriefing rooms and a fireproof gear room! We operate all year round. We offer reserve packs too!

properties.name: Tobati Aventuras Aereas
properties.description: Tobati Adventures is available all year round. Normally, operating a Cessna 206. There is camping available on the dropzone. The dropzone is located near the city of Tobati. To get to the dropzone from Asuncion, take route 2 towards Ciudad del Este until you get to Caacupe, then take the detour towards Tobati. Once in Tobati you will pass the town church. Take the second right and go 3 km. The dropzone will be on the left.

properties.name: Olimpic Skydive
properties.description: Open Wednesday, Friday and weekends. From Wroclaw city take Rt 35 southwest 25 km or take the Pietrzykowice Exit from Highway A-4. Calendar on our website lists events.

properties.name: Skydive Algarve
properties.description: Skydive Algarve continues to be a favorite DZ for boogie-goers. We have three annual boogies--Christmas, Spring and Fall--and operate fast-climbing turbine aircraft to 14,000 ft over the beautiful beaches of the Portuguese Algarve region. Based on a municipal airfield the DZ facilities are ideal for month-long events for those jumpers looking for a family friendly "sun, sea & skydiving" location. Jumps on to the local beach is a highlight for many skydivers who attend. Always contact the DZ to check activity between annual boogies.

properties.name: Skydive Europe
properties.description: Skydive Europe is a new drop zone in Portugal, open 7 days a week, year round. From capital city Lisbon, take the highway A-2 south to exit 10 to Beja/Ferreira do Alentejo. Go straight until Figueira dos Cavaleiros Airfield. Our aircraft is a brand new PAC 750XL, excellent for team training. We are proud to have helpful friendly staff. Coaching available in Formation skydiving, Freefly, Atmo, etc. We also have great facilities with WiFi, bar, relaxing area, lagoon etc. Just show up and enjoy!

properties.name: Skydive Portugal
location: ER254 Estrada de Viana Do Alentejo
properties.description: Skydive Portugal is an experienced drop zone and school dedicated to professional and fun skydiving. Open year-round and strategically located in Evora-the UNESCO capital of Alentejo. Located only 50 min away from Lisbon by car, 220km from Paro, and 400km from Oporto. Skydive Portugal is already the reference for skydivers all around the world! From seasonal boogies to special events, at Skydive Portugal all disciplines are welcome. Instruction and coaching are available from our highly trained and friendly staff.

properties.name: Skydive Transilvania
properties.description: DZ is in the heart of Transilvania. Open weekends; weekdays by appt. Close to tourist excursions (Salt Mines and Sibiu). Facilities for skydiver and non-skydiver (fishing pond, outside bar, small beach for swimming, adventure park for kids). Disco on weekends with loads of locals and fun!

properties.name: Timisoara Parachute Club
properties.description: Timisoara is Romania's 3rd largest city and this new DZ is located within easy reach. We are open, May through October, to all jumpers on weekends, public holidays and occasionally midweek. Take the DN709, 28 km out of Arad. The DZ is on your left just before the beautiful hill town of Siria.

properties.name: TNT-Brothers Dropzone
properties.description: Open March to December, Friday to Sunday. Air conditioned bar with snacks, beverages and warm food. Hangar with packing area and heated video, course and rigger rooms as well as a large room to hang out and debrief. Coaching available for intermediate formation skydiving, freefly, performance canopy piloting and accuracy.

properties.name: Skydive Vatulino
properties.description: Open on weekends and holidays. During summer, open almost everyday. Style and Accuracy, Canopy Piloting, FF, FS, Wingsuit coaches (english speaking) are available. 1200m Hop 'n Pop. 4000m for the rest. Check web page for events and directions.

properties.name: Skydive Beograd
properties.description: Open on weekends. On-call during weekdays, year round. From Belgrade city, take Zrenjaninski Road via Pancevacki Bridge, North bound. Public transportation, bus #101 available. Coaching available in FA and S&A.

properties.name: Skydive Empuriabrava
properties.description: Open seven days a week all year. Situated 1.5 hours north of Barcelona on the Costa Brava. Just 2km from the Mediterranean Sea in Empuriabrava with many hotels, apartments, and restaurants within walking distance. Wind Tunnel and Team Training facilities on site. Coaching and training from basic to advanced levels offered. Note: All skydivers are required to use AADs.

properties.name: Skydive Gran Canaria
location: San Agustin, Las Palmas de Gran Canaria, 35107
30 miles S of Las Palmas de Gran Canaria
properties.description: Open seven days a week, year round. From the capital city, Las Palmas de Gran Canaria and also from Gran Canaria Airport, take Hwy GC1 south to the exit- 46.5 km. Transport service available from DZ on the beach to the airfield. Restaurants and coffee shops at DZ. Friendly and very professional staff.

properties.name: Skydive Lillo
properties.description: Skydive Lillo is ideally situated close to Madrid, but just outside the Madrid control area. We are only 96 km from Madrid and open 7 days a week!

properties.name: Skydive Madrid
properties.description: Open seven days a week year round. 2 Pilatus Porters. 64 km from Madrid using free motorway A-IV. Hotel and restaurants located at the drop zone. Closest drop zone to Madrid City offering a very friendly staff, shop, packers and riggers. Modern facility with a great night life.

properties.name: Skydive Spain
properties.description: Skydive Spain continues to expand striving to offer the ultimate skydiving experience. Host to many events throughout the year including the Funshine Boogie, ToraTora events, Nordic events and many local activities too. With fast climbing turbine aircraft to 15, 000 feet every load, we are the ideal jumper's DZ. Open seven days a week with consistently great weather, huge landing area, indoor parking and friendly helpful staff.

properties.name: Ecole de Parachutisme de Chateau-d'Oex
properties.description: A small, but beautiful DZ at the foot of the Alps. The land of the flying cows!

properties.name: Bird's Paradise Extreme Resort
properties.description: We are a full-time DZ in South East Asia, and easily accessed from Bangkok. Complete skydiving instruction and new rentals are offered. We also offer a large variety of additional activities on-site. We have luxury accommodations available.

properties.name: Thai Sky Adventures, Ltd.
properties.description: Thailand's only full time DZ operating turbine aircraft for experienced skydivers and offering Tandem and AFF training for student skydivers. Great weather year-round and prices that you won't believe. Check out our website for details: www.thaiskyadventures.com

properties.name: Skydive Dubai Desert Campus
properties.description: Open Tuesday through Sunday year round from 8am until 5pm. From Dubai, take Hwy 66 (Dubai - Al Ain Road), Exit 47 (Margham). AFF, Tandem, Coaching, Tandem Instructor Courses, Coaching Courses, Wingsuit Courses,Load Organizing. Air Conditioned Packing Facility. This is Skydive Dubai's student training campus, AFFIC. We also have a Wind Tunnel! We have a hotel and Paintball Park too!

properties.name: Skydive Caribbean
properties.description: From Caracas, take Hwy Gran Mariscal de Ayacucho to Caucagua. Take Hwy Caucagua-Higuerote to Higuerote city. It is about 1 1/2 hours from Caracas--100 km. AFF, Tandem, and coaching available. Gear rental also available. We have a 207 Cessna with a retractable door. Come make a jump and see a great view of the ocean!
